Description: Neck sherd of black-figured North Ionian pottery krater; interior glazed with three red bands lined in white; exterior, top right of neck panel with much of a duck facing left in thick filling ornament.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B102.12)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.517)
